<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!--
	Restack intentionally omits com.apple.security.app-sandbox.

	Restack drives the Accessibility (AXUIElement) API to read and move the
	windows of OTHER applications, and uses NSWorkspace to launch/activate
	other apps. Both require the ability to send Apple Events / AX requests
	across process boundaries to arbitrary target apps chosen by the user at
	runtime. The App Sandbox restricts inter-app AX control and Apple Event
	messaging to a fixed, pre-declared set of targets (via
	com.apple.security.temporary-exception.apple-events / AEInteractWithClient),
	which is incompatible with a general-purpose window manager. Sandboxing
	Restack would break its core feature, so it ships as a non-sandboxed,
	Developer ID-distributed, Hardened Runtime app instead (notarization does
	not require sandboxing).

	No other entitlements are needed: Restack does not use JIT, unsigned
	executable memory, DYLD env vars, or any hardened-runtime exception, so
	this file is otherwise empty.
	-->
</dict>
</plist>
